# Diagram Examples

This repository demonstrates how to write and share Mermaid diagrams.

## Flowchart
```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Start] --> B{Is task clear?}
    B -- Yes --> C[Draft mermaid diagram]
    B -- No --> D[Review requirements]
    C --> E[Commit changes]
    D --> B
```

## Sequence Diagram
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant A as Agent
    participant G as Git

    U->>A: Request a Mermaid diagram
    A->>U: Draft example and confirm
    A->>G: Commit & push
    G-->>U: Change available in repo
```

## Tips
- Edit diagrams in any Markdown-compatible editor that supports Mermaid preview.
- Keep diagrams small and readable; use descriptive node labels.
- After changes, run `git status` to verify files, then commit and push.
